3.11.24  9:57 pm   in search for peace by mccoy tyner, he plays a chord with D in the bass, C, F, Bb in the middle, and Eb in the melody. it doesn't feel like an inversion of a Bb chord at all though. and in fact it sounds bad if you put the F too close to the bass, it doesn't work as well because it starts to sound like Bbmaj7add9 or Dmin7, whereas if you add a F# near the bass instead it sounds really cool (but omitting the F# makes it sound more relaxed and airy). meaning that using conventional notation this would maybe be called 'D7#5#9no3', and maybe even throw a b9 and b5 in there as well because the Bb turns into an Ab after a second. but this is super long and messy, so i propose we call this Dâ˜®, pronounced D-peace. what do you think of the chord?
